========,1,preface.
Mineral is a census-designated place (CDP) in Tehama County, California, United States.
The population was 123 at the 2010 census, down from 143 at the 2000 census.
========,2,Geography.
Mineral is located at (40.355686, -121.567333).
According to the United States Census Bureau, the CDP has a total area of , of which, of it is land and of it (0.25%) is water.
========,3,Climate.
This region experiences warm (but not hot) and dry summers, with no average monthly temperatures above 71.6 °F.
According to the Köppen Climate Classification system, Mineral has a warm-summer Mediterranean climate, abbreviated "Csb" on climate maps.
